title: Grateful Dead Live at Jefferson Civic Center Coliseum on 1995-04-05
description: Touch Of Gray, Wang Dang Doodle, Stagger Lee, Me & My Uncle*-> Maggie's Farm*, Row Jimmy, The Music Never Stopped Here Comes Sunshine, Way To Go Home, Truckin'-> That Would Be Something-> Uncle John's Band-> Mathilda**-> Drums**-> Space-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
no that last review was in the wrong show(i meant it for 1980-06-21 in anchorage -- an awesome show)

this show. yeah i cant say much for 1995. jerry sounds beautiful on his slower tunes like so many  roads, black muddy river,  days between....its clear jerry's gas tank is running empty. this show doesnt sound all that bad. its worth a stream, not a download

four stars (only relative to the other shows from 95 that ive heard)

Birminghasm-ham Jerome Overdrive An up-beat Uncle John's Band that jammed out on for upinta 13 minutes before da steel drums lead into Matilda...we thought we was in the Islands Mon!!

Penultimately this evening was Jerry's epic Morning Dew effort, hallerin' at the top of his voice about whether or not "it matters".  News Flash!!! IT DON'T !!!

For overall without-a-net high-flying trapeze jamming I rate this as a strong show. Only drawback was it was so short we were on the tie-dyed streets of B'Ham again in short order.
Great energy show with lots of surprises!!

2nd best show i ever saw wow, i mean ok i was 17 when i toured and yes i had only seen 94 n 95 shows in my whole riff with this scene...but damn! this was so great this night! jerry smiled thruout! anyhow, as for the song content, touch is great, nice guitar and finish, row jimmy feels it, but the 2nd set is where it takes off....hcs is beautiful, long way whatever, truckin misses durin the song, but u can just hear the note at the end jam, and the show takes off from there, wow! 95 or not, from there this show is f'in amazing!!!! uj's band is so different from others but rocks, then matilda! wow! d+s sure, but the miracle and then the morning dew to beat all m dews! i have listened to SO many mdews and by FAR this is jerry's most amazing singing and I WAS THERE!!!!! it was F'IN the best, most heart wrenchin moment of my g d tourin career, fo real! jbg is ok at the end, but tears were for the m dew and knowin jerry was on his way out, how he sang those notes....5 stars for sure!!!!
